For the record, this is because women usually try to commit suicide via indirect means. Slitting their wrists or overdosing on medication, that kind of thing. "Leaving a pretty corpse," as it were. These methods are 1) unreliable and 2) can take long enough that they can be saved if someone gets to them in time.

Men, on the other hand, choose direct methods when taking their own lives. Guys prefer shooting themselves or jumping off of extreme heights to their deaths, the kind of things that both get instant results and can't be taken back once done. Though, it should be said that you CAN fuck up shooting yourself in the head; I've seen pictures of dudes missing their jaws and other bits of their face, but still very much alive as they were loaded into ambulances. Dudes looked like creatures from S.T.A.L.K.E.R.

Another thing to consider is that many suicide -attempts- are 'heat of the moment' kind of deals, where both the decision to kill themselves and the act of trying to do so occur within a twelve hour span (Which may be the case for our Anon here, actually). These are usually your more sloppier and less successful suicides, as premeditated and planned suicide attempts (the kind that give off the signals suicide prevention groups tell you to look out for, like giving away possessions and tying up loose ends) tend to be successful. Again though; guys will go to the more sure-fire methods, so there are a lot of male suicides that likely could have been avoided if something, anything, convinced the guy to at least take a nap or a long drive before putting the gun against their temple.

One bad day, a reliable method, and no distractions is all it takes for some people to kill themselves.
